reviews: I bought the 2 pack of black & white for golfing. 1 golf belt is anywhere from $20-$80 so this was a great deal for 2. They're super comfortable and not too bulky being a woman. My only negative complaint is there's no instructions on how to open the belt to "cut to fit". Thankfully I figured it out but for someone who has never used a canvas belt before I didn't really understand. All the instructions online say is "open belt & cut to fit". You will need pliers or a butter knife to pry open the back as you can't do it by hand. Other then that the actual belt is great :)
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: No more pants on the ground
reviews:
Bought for the other half and he is more than pleased with this belt. It's well made and the automatic buckle works great. Other belts are thick and cause pressure on the lower back, this one is thinner but not too thin to affect quality and does not put added pressure on back. The colour said navy and it is navy. I will no doubt be ordering him another in the coming months. There are a number of colour choices to match your wardrobe.
Quick shipping, price was right and exactly as described by seller.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Belt adjusts easily for my Keto weight loss
reviews:
I'm losing weight gradually everyday while on Keto. These belts are so easy to adjust whenever I go down a waist size. I just snip off the buckle end of the canvas strip, then reattach to the buckle, and voila... the belt fits me perfectly again!
I move around a lot in my line of work, and so I worried that the buckle might not withstand the strain I force on a belt when I'm at my job, but the clasp stays snapped on thru my entire shift.
I'm really impressed with the durability and flexibility of these belts. I might order more, in different colors, so I have more variety lol. My purchase was for the grey/blue/yellow 3-pack belts.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Looks good. Strong material and long for large sizes.
reviews:
Happy with the product if you've seen one of these types of belts they're all kind of the same.

I am a size 38 Costco jeans and the belt has tons of extra. I have enough to almost goto my left side belt loop so like 14-16 inches extra left of the buckle. Should be no problem for someone like 8-10" bigger than me. Will continue to buy as the teeth on the buckle usually wear out. That's just how these belts are if you wear them tight.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Good product - quick delivery - quite happy with it.
reviews: Wore one of mine for the first time yesterday - felt it was excellent in all regards, except one - the metal 'tab' at the end I found quite difficult to thread through the belt loops - perhaps if it was pointed or the corners rounded it would be easier. Also, I would like to have a sliding loop to hold the excess length, but that's not really critical - just would be handy.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Simple Belts that will Last a While

I like the simplicity of these buckles and if you have not tried out belts like these I would urge you to.

reviews: This belt is terrific! It is adjustable and you can cut it if necessary. Love the size as it fits perfectly. The belt buckle is black metal. reviews:

I admit I have a bit of a belly (thus the adjustable belt), but when I snug up the belt my stomach rubs against that sharp metal clasp. It's OK for a bit, and after a few hours the chaffing and scratching is too much.

I never thought that would be an issue. I will try a plastic clasped belt next.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Should Include Cutting Instructions With Belts
reviews: Product came without cutting instructions and on the first belt I cut the length big enough for my waist but with only 2-3"s to spare. I believe the recommended extra length is 5". From the get-go, the metal piece at the cut end keeps popping open so can create an embarrassing moment. For the next two, I referred back online at the Amazon site and I cut with an extra 5"s and haven't had the same problem with the other two belts.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Works OK but older style better
reviews: I've worn a number of web belts over the years. Older versions had a sliding pin inside the buckle which pressed against the belt tail to hold it in place with friction. You could adjust the belt circumference by tugging the tail to loosen the pin. This new design has you open the buckle to remove its teen from the belt's webbing. It's a more economical design, stamped sheet metal vs a separate pin. It works but I find having to open the buckle and snap it closed kind of annoying.
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

reviews: Love the colour on this belt, and always get random compliments. Unless you happen to be XXXL, you'll need to cut the webbing down to size. That means prying off the metal piece at the end, which doesn't go back quite as easily and always seems to be coming loose. An equally effective alternative to stop fraying is to hold a lighter close to the end until the fibres start melting, then squish them together with a pair of pliers
product_name: Cut To Fit Canvas Web Belt Size Up to 52" with Flip-Top Solid Black Military Buckle (Black)

review_title: Somewhat low quality but you get what you pay for

But, overall if you're looking for an inexpensive casual belt to keep your pants up this is not a bad way to go. I like the fact that there are two colours in the same package, and I like the way they fit and can be adjusted to any size.

reviews:
The clip for the end of the belt fell off within two days. The actual belt buckle didn't want to clip properly at first, but after a week of wearing seemed to finely wear in and start clipping all the way in. I'm returning it because it looks funny with the cut end having nothing to cover it.

At about the year mark the belt clip just straight out broke. This was on probably wearing it once a week over the last 52 weeks. So, not the most rugged built belt, but what do you expect for $10
